  "prompt": "Google interview again?",
  "response": "Yes, you can reapply to Google after being rejected from a previous interview, but there are some important things to keep in mind:\n\n1. **Cooling-off Period**: Google typically has a **6-12 month waiting period** before you can reapply. This gives you time to improve your skills and address any gaps identified during your previous interview.\n\n2. **Reflect on Feedback**: If you received feedback from your previous interview, use it to identify areas for improvement. Focus on strengthening weak areas, whether it\u2019s coding, system design, or behavioral skills.\n\n3. **Prepare Thoroughly**: Treat the reapplication as a fresh start. Practice coding problems (especially on platforms like LeetCode), review system design concepts, and refine your behavioral responses. Google interviews are rigorous, so preparation is key.\n\n4. **Show Growth**: Highlight any new skills, projects, or experiences you\u2019ve gained since your last interview. Demonstrating growth can strengthen your application.\n\n5. **Reapply with Confidence**: When you\u2019re ready, submit your application again. Be honest about your previous attempt and express your enthusiasm for the role and the company.\n\nGood luck! Persistence and preparation can make a big difference in your next attempt.",
